    title: 'Professional Business Channel',
    text: "AI WhatsApp runs on your business number. Facade specifications, tender confirmations, and material orders stay separated from personal messaging."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Can the AI assess panel damage from photos?",
    answer: "The AI cannot perform structural or fire assessment from images — only a qualified cladding professional on-site can evaluate panel integrity, fixing condition, and fire classification. It does, however, respond productively to every photograph — acknowledging the visible damage, asking about the panel material (composite, fibre cement, timber, or metal), the building height, and whether any panels are loose and posing a safety risk. Every image attaches to your lead for professional assessment during your site inspection."
  },
  {
    question: "What about evolving programme threads?",
    answer: "Cladding programmes evolve continuously — a main contractor sends elevation drawings, then confirms the SFS completion date, then adjusts the cladding start by a week, then adds a canopy variation. The AI maintains the complete conversation history and compiles every update into one consolidated facade lead with material, area, programme, and variations."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does AI WhatsApp cost for cladding contractors?",
    answer: `WhatsApp is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as a channel add-on. A domestic timber cladding job generates £2,000 to £8,000. A commercial rainscreen package generates £50,000 to £500,000. Securing one main contractor's facade programme through a rapid WhatsApp reply — while you aligned panels on the MEWP at another site — covers the channel cost immediately.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I take over a WhatsApp conversation?",
    answer: "Post one reply in any thread and the AI transfers control to you for that conversation permanently. Most cladding contractors let the AI gather the initial scope — system type, material, area, building height, fire compliance, and programme — then engage directly to discuss the site measurement, detail solutions, and tender pricing."
  },
  {
    question: "How is WhatsApp data from cladding enquiries protected?",
    answer: "Every WhatsApp message — facade photographs, building locations, material specifications, fire compliance details, and sender contact information — is encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Your data stays exclusively with you. No project specifications reach competing cladding firms or are repurposed for any secondary use."
  }
